quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  3,122,"˹Remember˺ when two groups among you ˹believers˺ were about to cower, then God reassured them. So in God let the believers put their trust"
  3,123,"Indeed, God made you victorious at Badr when you were ˹vastly˺ outnumbered. So be mindful of God, perhaps you will be grateful"
  3,124,"˹Remember, O Prophet,˺ when you said to the believers, “Is it not enough that your Lord will send down a reinforcement of three thousand angels for your aid?”"
  3,125,"Most certainly, if you ˹believers˺ are firm and mindful ˹of God˺ and the enemy launches a sudden attack on you, God will reinforce you with five thousand angels designated ˹for battle˺"
  3,126,"God ordained this ˹reinforcement˺ only as good news for you and reassurance for your hearts. And victory comes only from God—the Almighty, All-Wise—"
  3,127,"to destroy a group of the disbelievers and humble the rest, causing them to withdraw in disappointment"
  3,128,"You ˹O Prophet˺ have no say in the matter. It is up to God to turn to them in mercy or punish them, for indeed they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To God ˹alone˺ belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  3,130,"O believers! Do not consume interest, multiplying it many times over. And be mindful of God, so you may prosper"
  3,131,Guard yourselves against the Fire prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,"Obey God and the Messenger, so you may be shown mercy"